ame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Aldford was born about 1120, in England. He had at least 2 sons with Mary fitzRichard. He died about 1160, at the age of 42."},"et":{"about 1120–Abt 1160":"umbes 1120–umbes 1160","1121–1185":"1121–1185","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1145–1213":"1145–1213","1120–1160":"1120–1160","1213":"1213","Abt 1145":"umbes 1145","1145":"1145","1121":"1121","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"umbes 1160","1160":"1160","about 1120":"umbes 1120","1180":"1180","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1120–Abt 1160":"noin 1120–noin 1160","1121–1185":"1121–1185","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1145–1213":"1145–1213","1120–1160":"1120–1160","1213":"1213","Abt 1145":"noin 1145","1145":"1145","1121":"1121","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"noin 1160","1160":"1160","about 1120":"noin 1120","1180":"1180","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1120–Abt 1160":"environ 1120–environ 1160","1121–1185":"1121–1185","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1145–1213":"1145–1213","1120–1160":"1120–1160","1213":"1213","Abt 1145":"environ 1145","1145":"1145","1121":"1121","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"environ 1160","1160":"1160","about 1120":"environ 1120","1180":"1180","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert de Aldford est né environ 1120, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 2 fils avec Mary fitzRichard.